CNH Industrial N.V. (NYSE:CNHI) Experiences Light Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
CNH Industrial N.V. (NYSE:CNHI) Experiences Light Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





(NYSE:CNHI) shares saw light trading volume with 177K shares changing hands by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Trading volume was down 85.55% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   Meag Munich Ergo Kapitalanlagegesellschaft Mbh reduced its investment by shedding 192,469 shares a decrease of 18.3%. Meag Munich Ergo Kapitalanlagegesellschaft Mbh claims 857,902 shares worth $9,599,000. The value of the position overall is down by 5.2%. As of quarter end Meag Munich Ergo Assetmanagement Gmbh had sold  a total of 13,474 shares trimming its stake by 76.5%. The value of the investment in (CNHI) went from $170,000 to $47,000 a change of $123,000 for the reporting period.
 As of the end of the quarter Aperio Group, LLC had acquired 16,974 shares growing its position 3.9%. The value in dollars increased from $4,232,000 to $5,189,000 increasing 22.6% since the last quarter. Exane Derivatives trimmed its ownership by selling 60 shares a decrease of 22.4% as of 06/30/2017. Exane Derivatives owns 208 shares with a value of $91,000. The total value of its holdings increased 15.2%.
  On July 13, 2017 the stock rating was changed to a “Buy” in a report from Seaport Global up from the previous “” rating. On June 19 the stock rating was upgraded to “Buy” from “Buy” by analysts at Bank of America.
 On November 28 the company was set at “Neutral” by PiperJaffray which was a boost from the previous “Underweight” rating. October 12 investment analysts at Deutsche Bank held the company rating at “Underweight” but raised the price target from $6.40 to $7.00.
 On October 12 Barclays maintained a company rating of “Underweight” and raised the price target  to $7.00 from $5.00. On September 7 analysts at Deutsche Bank added the stock to its research portfolio by announcing an initial rating of “Sell” and projecting a price target of $6.40.
 The company is so far trading up by 0.34% since yesterday’s close of $11.65.  The company also recently declared a dividend paid on Tuesday the 2nd of May 2017.  The dividend payment was $0.030 per share for the quarter or $0.12 annualized.  The dividend yield was $1.03.  The ex-dividend date was set for Monday the 24th of April 2017. 





 It is trading at $11.69 which is marginally higher than the 50 day moving average of $11.55 and marginally over the 200 day moving average of $10.32.  The 50 day moving average went up by +1.19% whereas the 200 day moving average was up $1.37 or +13.30%. 
 The most current P/E ratio is 51.96 and market cap is 15.93B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $0.22 and is projected to be $0.43 for the current year with 1,362,981,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.07 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $0.55. 
 CNH Industrial N.V. designs, produces, markets, sells, and finances agricultural and construction equipment, trucks, commercial vehicles, and buses worldwide. It also offers specialty vehicles for firefighting, defense, and other uses; engines, transmissions, and axles for its vehicles. The Agricultural Equipment segment provides farm machinery and implements, including two-wheel and four-wheel drive tractors, crawler tractors, combines, cotton pickers, grape and sugar cane harvesters, hay and forage equipment, planting and seeding equipment, soil preparation and cultivation implements, and material handling equipment. This segment offers its products under the New Holland Agriculture, Case IH Agriculture, Steyr, and Miller brand names. The Construction Equipment segment offers excavators, crawler dozers, graders, wheel loaders, backhoe loaders, skid steer loaders, compact track loaders, and telehandlers, under the New Holland Construction and Case Construction brand names. The Commercial Vehicles segment provides light, medium, and heavy vehicles for the transportation and distribution of goods under the Iveco brand name; commuter buses and touring coaches under the Iveco Bus and Heuliez Bus brand names; quarry and mining equipment under the Iveco Astra name; and firefighting vehicles under the Magirus brand name, as well as vehicles for civil defense and peace-keeping missions under the Iveco Defence Vehicles brand name. The Powertrain segment offers propulsion and transmission systems and axles for on-and off-road applications, as well as engines for marine application and power generation through the FPT Industrial brand. The Financial Services segment provides and administers retail financing to customers for the purchase or lease of new and used industrial equipment or vehicles, and other equipment; and wholesale financing, which consists primarily of floor plan financing to CNH Industrial dealers. CNH Industrial N.V. is based in London, the United Kingdom..






