Effective September 29, 2013. Fiat Industrial S.p.A. and CNH Global N.V. were merged into CNH Industrial N.V. CNH Industrial N.V. is a global corporation active in the agricultural and construction equipment businesses. Created in 1999 through the merger of New… MoreEffective September 29, 2013. Fiat Industrial S.p.A. and CNH Global N.V. were merged into CNH Industrial N.V. CNH Industrial N.V. is a global corporation active in the agricultural and construction equipment businesses. Created in 1999 through the merger of New Holland N.V. and Case Corporation, CNH is comprised of three agricultural brands (Case IH; New Holland Ag; Steyr) and two construction equipment brands (Case Construction Equipment; New Holland Construction). CNH Parts & Service division provides product support, while CNH Capital finances agricultural and construction organizations. CNH employs approximately 32,000 people worldwide and is a majority-owned subsidiary of Fiat Industrial S.p.A. with Italian headquarters located in Torino.
Company Overview
•Effective September 29, 2013. Fiat Industrial S.p.A. and CNH Global N.V. were merged into CNH Industrial N.V.
•CNH Industrial N.V. is a global corporation active in the agricultural and construction equipment businesses. Created in 1999 through the merger of New… MoreCompany Overview
•Effective September 29, 2013. Fiat Industrial S.p.A. and CNH Global N.V. were merged into CNH Industrial N.V.
•CNH Industrial N.V. is a global corporation active in the agricultural and construction equipment businesses. Created in 1999 through the merger of New Holland N.V. and Case Corporation, CNH is comprised of three agricultural brands (Case IH; New Holland Ag; Steyr) and two construction equipment brands (Case Construction Equipment; New Holland Construction). CNH Parts & Service division provides product support, while CNH Capital finances agricultural and construction organizations. CNH employs approximately 32,000 people worldwide and is a majority-owned subsidiary of Fiat Industrial S.p.A. with Italian headquarters located in Torino.

IT Structure
•The European Customer Service Center team supports approximately 11,000 internal business users and the external provider is IBM.
•There are two European Service Desks based in Vicenza, Italy, and Debrecen, Hungary. The two service desks support approximately 8,000 internal business users and the provider is T-Systems.

IT Vendors
• Athesys provides application management services.
•The SAP Service Desk is staffed by Accenture.





