CNH Industrial N.V. Key Developments

CNH Industrial N.V. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
Jul 26 17
CNH Industrial N.V. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net revenues of $6,948 million compared to $6,753 million for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes and equity in income of unconsolidated subsidiaries and affiliates was of $333 million compared to $241 million for the same period a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $242 million or $0.18 per basic and diluted share compared to $126 million or $0.10 per basic and diluted share for the same period a year ago. Net debt was $20,188 million as on June 30, 2017. Adjusted net income was $266 million or $0.19 adjusted diluted EPS against $216 million or $0.16 adjusted diluted EPS a year ago. Total operating profit was $523 million compared to $488 million for the same period a year ago. 

For six months, the company reported net revenues of $12,629 million compared to $12,125 million for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes and equity in income of unconsolidated subsidiaries and affiliates was of $412 million compared to loss of $229 million for the same period a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $288 million or $0.21 per basic and diluted share compared to net loss attributable to the company of $386 million or $0.28 per basic and diluted share for the same period a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $267 million against $478 million a year ago. Expenditures for property, plant and equipment and intangible assets, net of assets under operating lease and assets sold under buy-back commitments was $165 million against $172 million a year ago. Adjusted net income was $324 million or $0.23 adjusted diluted EPS against $217 million or $0.16 adjusted diluted EPS a year ago. Total operating profit was $780 million compared to $720 million for the same period a year ago. Capital expenditures were flat at $91 million.

For the year 2017, the company is leading its 2017 guidance for sales and EPS to the upper end of the range while keeping the net industrial debt guidance unchanged as net sales of Industrial Activities of approximately $24 billion, adjusted diluted EPS of approximately $0.41, net industrial debt at the end of 2017 between $1.4 billion and $1.6 billion. For the full year, the company expects CapEx guidance to be conformed up between 5% and 10% year-on-year.


CNH Industrial N.V. Names Alan Berger as Chief Technical Officer, Agricultural Equipment and Construction Equipment Product Development
Jun 30 17
CNH Industrial N.V. announced the appointment of Alan Berger as Chief Technical Officer, Agricultural Equipment and Construction Equipment Product Development.  In this role, Mr. Berger joins the Company's Group Executive Council (GEC), an operational decision-making body of CNH Industrial, which is responsible for reviewing the operating performance of the businesses and making decisions on certain operational matters. Alan Berger joined Case Corporation in 1996 as Chief Engineer for Case Construction. He has over 20 years of international product development experience in the off-highway vehicle industry, much of which he gained through roles of increasing importance with Volvo Construction Equipment culminating in the role of Senior Vice President, Technology. In September 2016, Mr. Berger re-joined CNH Industrial in the role of Chief Technical Officer, Agricultural Equipment Products.


CNH Industrial N.V. Announces the Launch of New Online Newsroom for the North American Region
Jun 15 17
CNH Industrial N.V. announced the launch of a new online Newsroom for the North American region. The Newsroom, media.cnhindustrial.com/NAFTA, features a media portal for members of the press and news outlets to access the best and most up to date information about CNH Industrial and five of its brands, Case IH, CASE Construction Equipment, New Holland Agriculture, New Holland Construction, and FPT Industrial. The Newsroom is designed to be the essential tool for obtaining the Latest News, Product Information and Global Communications from CNH Industrial and its brands. It serves journalists covering various beats by providing content on an array of sectors including: agricultural machinery, construction equipment, and powertrain technologies. Journalists on deadline are now able to quickly and easily access the latest corporate information on the company including Management Profiles, History, Publications, and Galleries, which are comprised of both still images and broadcast quality videos.


