l N.V. 2016-03-26 14:19 PDTOther Employee Reviews for CNH Industrial N.V. Apr 10, 2016 Helpful (7)"Something is Wrong on the Inside"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Racine, WICurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Racine, WIDoesn't RecommendNegative OutlookDisapproves of CEOI have been working at CNH Industrial N.V. full-timeProsGreat place to learn how not to run a business.ConsTop engineers and managers keep quitting. Termination in overdrive.CNH RMO has cultural and structural flaws.You need to manage and cultivate your culture if you’re going to build great products — and you can do this by treating employees with respect.Fiat's upper management needs to learn more about what’s going on at this facility and what’s bothering their employees.You have rampant discontent and discord within the hourly and salary personnel. This starts at the top. No camaraderie or teamwork exists. Don’t treat your employees as burdens.Cultural...This plants leadership doesn't set a good example when it comes to CNH business's core values.This plants morale is at rock bottom. Positive employee morale is usually exhibited by confidence, discipline and willingness to perform. High morale in the work place is essential to success and is mostly influenced from the top down rather than from the bottom up.Managers that create low morale in employees do so from a top-down command and control mode, which implies that employees’ do the listening and managers need not reciprocate. There is a gap at this plant in addressing the real problems, thus further exacerbate them.Employee distrust, disrespect towards management and reductions of morale and workforce motivation will be this plants downfall.Check the facts Fiat.A costly indicator of low morale is high turnover; when employees leave because they are not happy with their jobs and have few external reasons to stay. The proof is in the pudding. I need not go into details on why their leaving in droves.Structural...A company with a strong organizational structure benefits from improved communication, a well-defined hierarchy and the ability to create a unified company message. This plant has no efficient organizational structure. Internal conflict is the daily word. In order to maintain a strong company framework, you need to be able to identify the problems within an organizational structure and deal with them as they occur, without the "us versus them" mentality. I am truly disgusted.Advice to ManagementAlways treat your employee with respect and never as a burden. They’re more than dollars, they are your livelihood. Without them, you don’t have a business.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (7) CNH Industrial N.V. Response seconds agoEdit • Delete CNH Industrial N.V. 2016-04-10 10:33 PDT Mar 8, 2016"Overall Positive"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeRecommendsNeutral OutlookNo opinion of CEOI have been working at CNH Industrial N.V. full-timeProsGood Benefits and decent perks for field staff. Management has become very open to adapting to changing market.ConsBureaucratic overloads. Lots and lots and lots of busy work that distracts from the main goal: SALES. No opportunities for performance or annual raises. Incentive compensation system is to complicated to figure out and target growth for achievement is always obscenely obnoxious, intentionally.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) CNH Industrial N.V. Response seconds agoEdit • Delete CNH Industrial N.V. 2016-03-08 16:27 PSTReviews > CNH Industrial N.V. There are newer employer reviews for CNH Ind